Text:
...Weather's calm with a pleasant breeze. Perfect day
for fishing.

Good call avoiding the harbor and heading to a
secluded shore. Some token monsters around,
but nothing we can't handle.
...Oh darn! One swam off with the bait again!
This is inefficient...catching one fish at a time...
If only the fish were biting more today.
...Hyah.

Eta. If you don't put any bait on the hook before you
cast, the fish won't bite.

What if we made...some sort of fake bait...that
tricks the fish...into biting?
You're talking about lures. I didn't bring any today.

So we've gotta keep hooking on these slimy things
each time...and we can only catch...one fish...at a
time?
That's the point of fishing.
What a hassle...

...Well, guess that's one way to look at it. But I
think a relaxing activity outdoors once in a
while is a nice change of pace.

Zeta, do you know how much a large Midgar tuna sells
for?

Depends on the season and circulation, but a large
tuna usually goes for around 1 million zeni per fish.

Then taking into account the various expenses, you'd
be left with, say, 500,000 zeni.

The income of a single fisherman is way too unstable
to fund the Garden.

Unless we form a fishery, it's unlikely to be a
viable business, and fishing itself relies heavily
on external circumstances.

It'd be an impractical strategy for the Garden as we
currently need to generate revenue systematically.
...All this business talk is the real "hassle."

You know, you two should try and relax a littleâ€”um,
Eta?
...Done.
What is?
A slime grenade.
A grenade?!

If we blow up...the ocean surface...lots of dead
fish...will float up.
Wait, dooon't!!!
In you go.
You've gotta be kidding...
Ooh...look at all the fishes floating to the surface.
All I see are a bunch of mangled carcasses...!
Thanks for also provoking the nearby monsters.
Desperate times...call for...wasteful measures!

Eta...I think I'm starting to grasp exactly what kind
of girl you are!

...Looks like the monsters' attacks have subsided for
now.
Seriously, a little more common senseâ€”
Gamma...calm down.

You're the last person who should be telling me that!
Zeta, say something to her!

...No need to get worked up. Let's take it easy and
cast in those fishing lines. You know, moments like
this can give birth to inspiration.
Zetaâ€”
...Well, not that I'm making any promises.
Hmph!

As for you, Eta, no more exploding the ocean. It
makes the fish flee from this nice, secluded area.
Mm...fine.
Whew...what a lot of fuss over a simple fishing trip.

Well, we're just getting started, so let's try and
make the most of it.
